abstract: The Jets beat the Dolphins decisively, but the feeling persists that they did not play that well.
snippet: The Jets beat the Dolphins decisively, but the feeling persists that they did not play that well.
lead_paragraph: The prevailing emotion in the Jets' locker room late Monday night after they beat the hapless Miami Dolphins, 24-6, was that of relief. Never has being an average team with a 3-3 record felt so good.

headline.main: Much-Needed Win for Jets, but What Does It Mean?
